  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "When will Adobe XD be available for Windows?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **Adobe XD is fully available for Windows**. You can download and install it through the Adobe Creative Cloud application or directly from the [Adobe XD webpage](https://www.adobe.com/products/xd.html).\n\n### How to Get Adobe XD on Windows:\n\n1. **Adobe Creative Cloud Subscription**:\n   - **Subscription Plans**: Adobe XD is available as part of various Creative Cloud plans, including individual, business, and student plans. Depending on your needs, you can choose a plan that best suits you.\n   - **Download via Creative Cloud**:\n     1. **Install the Creative Cloud Desktop App**: If you haven't already, download and install the [Creative Cloud desktop application](https://www.adobe.com/creativecloud/desktop-app.html).\n     2. **Sign In**: Open the Creative Cloud app and sign in with your Adobe ID.\n     3. **Find Adobe XD**: Navigate to the \"Apps\" section and locate Adobe XD.\n     4. **Install**: Click the \"Install\" button next to Adobe XD to begin the installation process.\n\n2. **Free Starter Plan**:\n   - Adobe offers a free starter plan for Adobe XD, which includes limited features but is sufficient for getting started. You can sign up for the free plan on the [Adobe XD Free Plan page](https://www.adobe.com/products/xd/free-trial.html).\n\n### System Requirements:\n\nEnsure your Windows PC meets the following minimum system requirements for optimal performance:\n\n- **Operating System**: Windows 10 or later (64-bit versions only)\n- **Processor**: Intel\u00ae or AMD processor with 64-bit support; 2 GHz or faster processor\n- **RAM**: 4 GB minimum (8 GB recommended)\n- **Storage**: 4 GB of available hard-disk space\n- **Screen Resolution**: 1280 x 800 display\n- **Graphics**: GPU with DirectX 10 support\n\n### Troubleshooting:\n\n- **Installation Issues**: If you encounter problems installing Adobe XD, try updating your Creative Cloud app or restarting your computer. Ensure that your Windows OS is up to date.\n- **Subscription Problems**: Verify that your Adobe subscription includes Adobe XD. Some plans may not cover all Adobe applications.\n- **Contact Support**: If issues persist, reach out to [Adobe Support](https://helpx.adobe.com/support.html) for personalized assistance.\n\n### Additional Resources:\n\n- **Tutorials and Guides**: Adobe offers a variety of [tutorials](https://helpx.adobe.com/xd/tutorials.html) and [resources](https://www.adobe.com/products/xd/resources.html) to help you get the most out of Adobe XD.\n- **Community Forums**: Engage with other users and find answers to common questions on the [Adobe Community Forums](https://community.adobe.com/).\n\nIf there have been any changes to Adobe XD's availability for Windows after October 2023, I recommend checking the [official Adobe website](https://www.adobe.com/products/xd.html) or contacting Adobe directly for the most up-to-date information.",
